01:08.864 --> 01:10.363
Malcolm.

01:10.399 --> 01:11.765
I'm here, Fiona.

01:11.801 --> 01:13.400
I'm here.

01:13.436 --> 01:15.869
[Labored breathing]

01:19.275 --> 01:22.075
[Grunting]

01:22.111 --> 01:25.745
[Screaming]

01:25.781 --> 01:28.449
[Baby crying]

01:39.128 --> 01:43.097
Midwife: It's a boy...
A healthy baby boy.

01:46.135 --> 01:48.502
You're beautiful.

01:55.344 --> 01:59.379
No, you're perfect.

01:59.415 --> 02:02.683
Now, we just need to
give him the perfect name.

02:10.960 --> 02:13.026
Who are you?

02:13.062 --> 02:14.627
We're fairies, dear.

02:14.663 --> 02:17.964
This is Tiger Lily, your
son's fairy godmother.

02:18.000 --> 02:20.467
I've read about fairy godmothers,

02:20.503 --> 02:23.070
and they always come alone.

02:25.474 --> 02:27.440
Is there something wrong?

02:27.476 --> 02:29.943
Quite the opposite.

02:29.979 --> 02:33.780
A prophecy told us that on
this darkest winter's night,

02:33.816 --> 02:36.483
a boy would be born
with great light magic.

02:36.519 --> 02:38.819
A child known...

02:42.124 --> 02:43.991
as the Savior.

02:58.040 --> 02:59.472
Well, that smells disgusting.

02:59.508 --> 03:00.473
What is that?

03:00.509 --> 03:02.442
A dragon egg that never hatched.

03:02.478 --> 03:04.511
And the dragon breath trapped inside

03:04.547 --> 03:06.980
is potent medicine indeed.

03:07.016 --> 03:08.648
And that's how you wake up Blue?

03:08.684 --> 03:10.450
With a dead baby dragon?

03:10.486 --> 03:12.152
That's dark even for the Dark One.

03:12.188 --> 03:14.088
Do you have a better idea, Miss Swan?

03:16.358 --> 03:18.292
That's the problem
with Saviors, isn't it?

03:21.330 --> 03:23.464
Never quite as helpful as advertised.

03:30.072 --> 03:31.638
[Inhales deeply]

03:36.412 --> 03:38.345
Well, I guess neither are you.

03:42.718 --> 03:43.984
[Door bells jingle]

03:49.058 --> 03:50.090
[Door bells jingle]

03:51.794 --> 03:53.660
Did that make you feel better?

03:53.696 --> 03:54.861
No.

03:54.897 --> 03:58.431
Look, this is about defeating
your mother, isn't it?

03:58.467 --> 04:00.567
Rumple, stop it.

04:00.603 --> 04:02.168
You're letting her get under your skin.

04:02.204 --> 04:03.904
She has Gideon's heart.

04:04.840 --> 04:07.040
I've already lost one son,
Belle. I can't lose another.

04:07.076 --> 04:10.077
And you won't... not as long
as his mother's drawing breath.

04:13.048 --> 04:14.815
He's so lucky to have you.

04:16.317 --> 04:19.652
But sometimes, I feel that...

04:19.688 --> 04:22.155
this is our family's fate...

04:22.199 --> 04:25.666
For parents and children
always to be torn apart.

04:25.694 --> 04:26.793
[Door bells jingle]

04:26.829 --> 04:29.062
Hey, guys, you might
want to get in here.

04:32.401 --> 04:34.968
Blue? It's Snow.

04:35.004 --> 04:36.036
Blue?

04:37.239 --> 04:38.438
Snow.

04:38.474 --> 04:39.439
Hey.

04:39.475 --> 04:41.407
Tiger Lily gave me half this wand.

04:41.443 --> 04:43.015
We need the other
half. Have you seen it?

04:43.017 --> 04:44.811
- Where is it?
- Hook.

04:44.847 --> 04:45.812
Give her a minute.

04:50.819 --> 04:54.721
The wand is... it's at
the center of Storybrooke.

04:56.225 --> 04:59.092
That's enough of that.

04:59.128 --> 05:01.895
We don't need you
sharing all your secrets.

05:03.165 --> 05:05.798
Mom? What are you doing?

05:05.834 --> 05:07.700
Oh, I'm not your mother, Emma.

05:07.736 --> 05:09.303
I'm his.

05:10.839 --> 05:12.872
Now back away, all of you.

05:12.908 --> 05:15.542
Fairies have such delicate necks.

05:15.578 --> 05:18.545
You should listen to her, Father.

05:18.581 --> 05:20.681
She always makes good on her promises.

05:22.384 --> 05:26.186
And what about the promise
of a mother to a son?

05:26.222 --> 05:28.021
Careful of your emotions, Rumple.

05:28.057 --> 05:30.089
They run strongly in our family...

05:30.125 --> 05:33.293
As Blue is about to find out.

05:35.531 --> 05:37.397
I'm sorry I had to do this, Father.

05:37.433 --> 05:38.632
Goodbye.

05:39.735 --> 05:44.437
I'm afraid your magic is
no longer any use to you.

05:44.473 --> 05:47.207
It's time to get your heart back.

05:51.947 --> 05:54.414
[Sighs] Bloody hell.

05:54.450 --> 05:56.416
It's hard to get used to, isn't it?

05:56.452 --> 05:58.017
The no-magic thing.

05:58.053 --> 05:59.886
- Do you want me to...
- No.

05:59.922 --> 06:01.054
I-I can't use you as a crutch.

06:01.056 --> 06:02.589
It was my choice to give up my magic,

06:02.625 --> 06:05.325
so... I have to learn this rubbish.

06:05.361 --> 06:08.795
Well, you know, I went 28
years without during the curse.

06:08.831 --> 06:10.330
And it seemed impossible at first.

06:10.366 --> 06:12.999
I mean, turning lights on by hand.

06:13.035 --> 06:15.201
It's barbaric... and exhausting.

06:15.204 --> 06:16.670
But it gets easier, I promise.

06:16.673 --> 06:17.470
I hope so.

06:17.506 --> 06:19.272
'Cause right now, I feel quite useless.

06:19.308 --> 06:21.775
No, Zelena, you're not useless.

06:21.810 --> 06:24.043
Your sacrifice saved all of us.

06:24.079 --> 06:25.778
But who am I gonna save now?

06:25.814 --> 06:28.414
I've just been soundly
defeated by Sniglar.

06:28.450 --> 06:29.415
Sniglar?

06:29.451 --> 06:31.018
Yeah. I didn't name it, Ikea did.

06:31.053 --> 06:36.389
And if those Swedes can best me,
when the Final Battle comes...

06:36.425 --> 06:38.125
how am I going to protect my daughter?

06:40.029 --> 06:41.761
I have a thought.

06:41.797 --> 06:45.465
♪

06:45.501 --> 06:47.500
Gideon, please.

06:47.536 --> 06:51.004
Tell me where the Black
Fairy is keeping your heart.

06:51.040 --> 06:52.839
You've resisted her before.

06:52.875 --> 06:55.708
And she punished me for it.

06:55.744 --> 06:58.211
She ordered me to feel this...

06:58.247 --> 07:00.179
[Groans]

07:00.215 --> 07:03.182
pain if I resist again.

07:03.218 --> 07:05.551
Belle, stop.

07:05.587 --> 07:07.976
I'm sorry. Are you okay?

07:10.025 --> 07:12.091
- [Door bells jingle]
- That was my parents.

07:12.127 --> 07:14.494
They're looking for the
other half of Blue's wand.

07:14.530 --> 07:15.795
Any luck in here?

07:15.831 --> 07:17.997
Not yet, but we've just begun.

07:18.033 --> 07:19.372
Well, can we hurry it up?

07:19.375 --> 07:22.288
Once my folks find that wand, I'm
gonna go after the Black Fairy.

07:25.207 --> 07:28.741
Belle, I may have a
way to speak to our son,

07:28.777 --> 07:32.545
but I need something from
you first... your trust.

07:32.581 --> 07:33.847
Do you trust me, Belle?

07:36.377 --> 07:38.576
I trust you'll do what's right for him,

07:38.620 --> 07:41.821
what's right for our family.

07:41.857 --> 07:44.691
Then I need you to watch
over us while we're gone.

07:44.727 --> 07:47.760
"Gone"? What the hell is that?

07:47.796 --> 07:49.162
The sands of Morpheus.

07:51.367 --> 07:54.200
Father... what are you doing?

07:54.236 --> 07:56.836
I'm going to the only place
I can speak to you, Gideon...

07:56.872 --> 07:58.271
Your dream realm.

07:59.808 --> 08:02.275
Oh, and, uh... Miss Swan,

08:02.311 --> 08:03.710
you get to come with us, too.

08:03.746 --> 08:07.080
♪

08:13.226 --> 08:15.300
Great. So, you're kidnapping me now.

08:15.339 --> 08:18.020
I'm doing what I have
to do to save my son.

08:18.056 --> 08:20.989
In this place, even the Black
Fairy cannot control him.

08:21.025 --> 08:22.425
The dream realm, huh?

08:22.460 --> 08:23.992
Thought there'd be, like, flying pigs

08:24.028 --> 08:25.527
or talking doughnuts or something.

08:25.563 --> 08:26.995
Well, if you're not impressed,

08:27.031 --> 08:28.464
I can leave you here
while I find Gideon.

08:28.466 --> 08:30.065
Where is he? Isn't this <i> his</i> dream?

08:30.101 --> 08:32.433
[Sighs] It's not that simple.

08:32.470 --> 08:34.804
- Dreams a-are a maze.
- Then why am I here?

08:34.839 --> 08:38.740
You are here to stop you from
doing anything back there.

08:38.775 --> 08:42.110
If you kill her or banish her
before I find my son's heart,

08:42.145 --> 08:44.780
he will be lost to me forever.

08:47.218 --> 08:49.251
You could have just told me that.

08:49.287 --> 08:52.988
Well, Saviors have the luxury
of always doing the right thing.

08:53.024 --> 08:54.289
I do not.

08:54.325 --> 08:55.557
Where is he out here?

08:55.593 --> 08:58.794
[Distant squeaking]

08:59.197 --> 09:01.763
[Indistinct singing]

09:01.799 --> 09:04.967
♪

09:14.579 --> 09:17.480
[Cradle creaking]

09:30.795 --> 09:34.163
[Indistinct singing]

09:36.134 --> 09:37.633
What is this place?

09:41.205 --> 09:43.438
I was born here...

09:43.474 --> 09:46.541
Not that it was ever much of a home,

09:46.577 --> 09:49.478
after my mother left.

09:49.514 --> 09:52.848
This isn't Gideon's dream, is it?

09:52.884 --> 09:53.916
It's yours.

09:56.354 --> 09:59.187
It would seem so.

09:59.223 --> 10:02.324
If you don't mind, I've, uh...
I've spent enough time here already.

10:02.360 --> 10:05.056
It may well be my dream, but...

10:05.080 --> 10:07.062
my son is still in here somewhere,

10:07.098 --> 10:08.597
and I intend to find him.

10:08.633 --> 10:12.535
Black Fairy: ♪ I cried and
called my sweet bairn's name ♪

10:13.504 --> 10:18.140
♪ But never saw sweet baby again ♪

10:21.179 --> 10:23.512
Fiona, careful. It's just me.

10:23.548 --> 10:25.380
And since when do you have a sword?

10:25.416 --> 10:30.219
Since I found out the truth
about my son, the Savior.

10:31.089 --> 10:34.089
Now I can't sleep, I can't eat.

10:34.125 --> 10:35.098
I'm sorry.

10:35.101 --> 10:37.159
I never should have given
you the book of prophecy.

10:37.161 --> 10:40.796
But you did, because a
mother deserves the truth.

10:40.832 --> 10:44.566
So now I know a great
evil is coming for my son,

10:44.602 --> 10:47.169
and in their Final
Battle, he will be killed.

10:49.474 --> 10:52.174
Did you bring those other books?

10:53.144 --> 10:54.242
Here.

10:54.278 --> 10:56.178
At this point, you've
read more fairy lore

10:56.214 --> 10:57.512
than most fairies.

10:57.548 --> 11:01.683
And I'll continue reading
until I find this great evil.

11:01.719 --> 11:05.320
I know that it will be born
in the same winter as my son,

11:05.356 --> 11:07.355
with a scar like a crescent moon.

11:07.391 --> 11:09.324
It's a fairy's job to protect him.

11:09.360 --> 11:11.359
Your job is to raise him.

11:11.395 --> 11:14.497
What I can do, no mere human can.

11:22.640 --> 11:27.242
It's terrifying how much
this little thing changes you,

11:27.278 --> 11:30.312
makes you soft and sharp all at once.

11:35.119 --> 11:37.753
Would you like to hold him?

11:39.423 --> 11:41.289
Oh.

11:41.325 --> 11:43.292
I'd love to.

11:45.563 --> 11:46.695
What are you doing?

11:46.731 --> 11:49.865
As you said, it is a
fairy's job to protect him.

11:49.901 --> 11:51.166
But you're not a fairy.

11:51.202 --> 11:53.369
A small and temporary problem.

11:53.404 --> 11:56.539
<i>Le sgiathan cumhachd draoidheil.</i>

12:00.344 --> 12:01.944
That's not possible.

12:04.715 --> 12:06.888
What is that? An escape plan.

12:08.276 --> 12:10.509
If things go wrong,

12:10.544 --> 12:13.088
you need to get the hell out
of town and make it to New York.

12:13.124 --> 12:16.424
Well, that's a nice idea
with one teensy hiccup...

12:16.460 --> 12:19.127
The only thing I know
how to drive is a broom.

12:19.163 --> 12:21.663
Then we're going to fix that.

12:21.699 --> 12:25.467
It's time for you to learn
the other kind of stick.

12:27.371 --> 12:29.104
- [Tires squeal]
- Ugh.

12:29.140 --> 12:30.873
[Sighs] Bloody hell!

12:31.976 --> 12:33.008
[Tires squeal]

12:34.312 --> 12:35.377
[Tires squeal]

12:35.413 --> 12:37.813
Whoa! Take it easy.

12:37.849 --> 12:40.315
Brake is on the left.
Gas is on the right.

12:40.351 --> 12:42.985
I know. They're just
really close together!

12:45.423 --> 12:46.988
Zelena!

12:47.024 --> 12:48.023
Oh!

12:49.060 --> 12:50.559
[Groans] It's pointless!

12:50.595 --> 12:52.961
I'll have to find another
way to protect Robin.

12:52.997 --> 12:54.964
Well, it's not just about Robin.

12:56.500 --> 12:59.634
It's about...

12:59.670 --> 13:01.136
Well, it's about Henry.

13:01.172 --> 13:02.637
Henry?

13:02.673 --> 13:04.039
When the Final Battle comes,

13:04.075 --> 13:05.908
he'll want to fight to the very end.

13:07.378 --> 13:11.981
But the thing about battles is,
not everyone makes it through.

13:13.918 --> 13:16.384
So...

13:16.420 --> 13:18.988
if we lose or...

13:20.491 --> 13:22.090
if there are casualties,

13:22.126 --> 13:25.361
he can't be anywhere near it.

13:27.531 --> 13:29.531
I need you to take him to New York

13:29.567 --> 13:33.101
where he will be safe and where...

13:33.137 --> 13:36.104
he can start a new life...

13:36.140 --> 13:37.339
with you.

13:39.677 --> 13:43.411
Regina, I-I don't know what to say.

13:43.447 --> 13:45.847
You'd really trust me to raise Henry?

13:45.883 --> 13:48.583
No, I trust him

13:48.619 --> 13:49.752
to raise you.

13:51.822 --> 13:53.822
Okay, then, let's do this.

13:53.858 --> 13:56.691
- [Engine starts]
- [Cellphone rings]

13:56.727 --> 13:58.293
[Sighs] Hello?

13:58.329 --> 14:00.395
Okay, Regina, time to
put on your mayor pants.

14:00.431 --> 14:01.464
Excuse me?

14:01.467 --> 14:03.198
Blue said that the wand is
at the center of Storybrooke,

14:03.200 --> 14:04.599
so we're here at the clock tower,

14:04.635 --> 14:06.101
the geographic center of Storybrooke.

14:06.103 --> 14:09.170
But there's nothing here,
except, you know, the clock.

14:09.206 --> 14:11.673
Well, slow down and tell
me what you want from me.

14:11.709 --> 14:13.608
You cast the curse, you made the town,

14:13.644 --> 14:15.277
you must know what Blue meant.

14:15.313 --> 14:18.680
Of course.

14:18.716 --> 14:20.982
The fairies breathe
love and hope, right?

14:21.018 --> 14:24.320
So when a fairy talks about
the center of Storybrooke...

14:24.355 --> 14:27.822
She means the heart of
Storybrooke... Granny's.

14:27.858 --> 14:29.391
Granny's.

14:29.427 --> 14:30.392
Let's go.

14:30.428 --> 14:31.593
Sorry, sis.

14:31.629 --> 14:33.195
You'll have to sit this one out.

14:36.867 --> 14:38.433
[Sighs]

14:38.469 --> 14:43.705
Black Fairy: ♪ Saw the
silent shadows did fall ♪

14:43.741 --> 14:48.243
♪ I cried and called
my sweet bairn's name ♪

14:48.279 --> 14:54.249
♪ But never saw sweet baby again ♪

14:54.285 --> 14:59.321
You know, I've been
keeping this down here

14:59.357 --> 15:01.189
just for you.

15:01.225 --> 15:05.827
I'm so happy we get a chance to play.

15:05.863 --> 15:07.562
You can't scare me, Fiona.

15:07.598 --> 15:09.297
Scare you?

15:09.333 --> 15:12.233
After all the pain you put me through?

15:12.269 --> 15:17.639
I'm going to do a lot
more than just scare you.

15:17.675 --> 15:22.344
Because I do need to know
where that wand is hidden.

15:22.380 --> 15:25.814
You can do what you
want to me, I won't talk.

15:25.850 --> 15:28.784
Who said anything about talking?

15:30.988 --> 15:33.588
There are other ways to get information

15:33.624 --> 15:36.157
out of that little head of yours,

15:36.193 --> 15:39.794
and they are so much more...

15:39.830 --> 15:41.529
fun.

15:41.565 --> 15:43.966
♪

16:05.497 --> 16:07.430
She's adorable.

16:07.466 --> 16:09.899
And she certainly doesn't look evil.

16:09.935 --> 16:12.368
That's what you said about
the last hundred babies.

16:12.404 --> 16:13.669
And I was right.

16:13.705 --> 16:15.371
Not one of them had this crescent scar

16:15.407 --> 16:16.772
you keep looking for.

16:16.808 --> 16:17.974
When do we stop?

16:18.010 --> 16:21.244
When I've checked every
child born this winter.

16:21.280 --> 16:24.680
Because one of them is
destined to kill my son.

16:24.716 --> 16:28.751
[Fusses]

16:28.787 --> 16:29.953
It's not her.

16:31.254 --> 16:33.656
I don't understand.

16:33.692 --> 16:35.891
That child had to be the one.

16:35.927 --> 16:38.494
Do you know what day it is today?

16:38.530 --> 16:41.298
It's the last day of winter,
and that was the last child.

16:44.703 --> 16:46.269
[Baby cooing]

16:46.305 --> 16:49.372
I'm sorry...

16:49.408 --> 16:51.808
but I will not fail you.

16:52.878 --> 16:56.746
We haven't tried everything... Not yet.

16:56.782 --> 16:58.682
What are you talking about?

17:00.585 --> 17:03.386
I found two ancient spells.

17:03.422 --> 17:07.189
It won't be easy, but
I think, with your help,

17:07.224 --> 17:09.659
I could combine them into
something very powerful.

17:09.694 --> 17:11.560
You want to create a new spell?

17:12.631 --> 17:13.663
That's forbidden.

17:13.699 --> 17:15.564
I can't, not even to help your son.

17:15.599 --> 17:18.000
This is about more than just my son.

17:18.036 --> 17:21.069
When this great evil arrives,
how many more will be hurt?

17:21.106 --> 17:24.240
Stop being afraid and help me.

17:26.444 --> 17:29.945
Everything I need is in
the Sacred Fairy Vault,

17:29.981 --> 17:33.482
and you can get me in.

17:33.518 --> 17:35.785
Do this with me,

17:35.821 --> 17:38.855
so no mother will ever
be ripped from her child.

17:47.799 --> 17:49.732
Emma: Want to tell me about your mom?

17:49.768 --> 17:51.667
Why were we just in her house?

17:51.703 --> 17:53.736
It's a figment of my subconscious.

17:53.739 --> 17:55.270
- It doesn't matter.
- I think it does.

17:55.273 --> 17:56.840
I was an orphan, too.
I know how this goes...

17:56.842 --> 17:58.841
One moment you hate them,
the next you miss them.

17:58.877 --> 18:01.110
I've been on that roller coaster.

18:01.146 --> 18:03.479
I just need to know that
when I go to defeat her,

18:03.515 --> 18:05.981
that you're really on my side.

18:06.017 --> 18:07.417
Are you serious?

18:08.920 --> 18:12.588
Do you really think
that was a fond memory,

18:12.624 --> 18:14.624
being back in that house?

18:14.659 --> 18:19.195
That woman never cared
for me, never loved me,

18:19.231 --> 18:23.599
never did one thing a mother should.

18:23.635 --> 18:26.169
She never even gave me a name.

18:28.240 --> 18:30.206
And when you defeat her,

18:30.242 --> 18:34.410
I won't shed a single tear.

18:34.446 --> 18:41.150
So, please, don't assume
we share the same story.

18:41.186 --> 18:43.386
I just want to find my son.

18:45.056 --> 18:46.689
Gideon: I think you already have.

18:46.725 --> 18:50.860
♪

19:03.642 --> 19:07.510
Thank you for fighting for me.

19:10.913 --> 19:13.781
I would do anything for you, son.

19:17.923 --> 19:22.158
Now... tell me where your heart is.

19:23.795 --> 19:26.395
[Sighs] I... I can't.

19:26.431 --> 19:28.764
I'm sorry.

19:28.800 --> 19:31.601
I don't know where it is.
She has it well-hidden.

19:36.374 --> 19:38.541
- Then we're lost.
- No.

19:38.577 --> 19:40.943
There is something here of use.

19:40.979 --> 19:43.346
The one thing she's afraid of...

19:43.381 --> 19:46.649
You learning her darkest secret.

19:46.685 --> 19:48.617
And what is that?

19:48.653 --> 19:51.387
The reason she gave you up.

19:53.725 --> 19:56.059
[Baby crying in distance]

20:11.843 --> 20:14.176
You've searched everywhere
for a way to defeat her,

20:14.212 --> 20:16.846
but I think all your
answers are right here,

20:16.882 --> 20:19.349
inside you.

20:21.553 --> 20:23.453
You just have to be
willing to face them.

20:27.325 --> 20:28.657
[Door bells jingle]

20:28.693 --> 20:31.400
Finally! Would you please
do something about her?

20:31.447 --> 20:33.295
I told you, it's important.

20:33.331 --> 20:34.930
So is my lunch rush.

20:34.966 --> 20:36.599
All right, people, let's
tear this place apart.

20:36.601 --> 20:37.800
Let's find that wand.

20:37.836 --> 20:40.737
♪

20:47.362 --> 20:48.461
[Sighs]

20:51.216 --> 20:53.283
- Jukebox?
- Jukebox.

21:11.036 --> 21:12.802
[Sighs] That's it.

21:14.706 --> 21:16.005
The other half, please.

21:16.041 --> 21:17.206
Well, hang on just a second.

21:17.242 --> 21:19.041
How do we know that
you are actually you?

21:19.077 --> 21:20.109
Because it's me.

21:20.145 --> 21:21.176
Wait. No. Hook's right.

21:21.212 --> 21:22.478
We should have a safe word or something.

21:22.480 --> 21:23.846
How do we know you're
not the Black Fairy?

21:23.848 --> 21:25.582
Black Fairy: Because <i> I</i> am.

21:27.452 --> 21:29.518
Right. Sorry I doubted you, love.

21:29.554 --> 21:31.887
That wand won't do you any good...

21:31.907 --> 21:33.940
Not without the Savior around.

21:33.992 --> 21:36.759
- Now, give it here.
- Unh-unh.

21:36.795 --> 21:39.261
My town, my rules.

21:39.297 --> 21:41.430
And you're not getting
this without a fight.

21:41.466 --> 21:44.166
[Sighs] I was hoping you'd say that.

21:44.202 --> 21:47.636
You know, I've done so
many dark things in my life,

21:47.672 --> 21:50.906
but I've never had a
chance to kill a queen.

21:50.942 --> 21:53.489
And I've never killed a fairy.

22:01.143 --> 22:03.309
I know you think you own this town,

22:03.345 --> 22:05.978
but I invented it... All of it.

22:06.014 --> 22:07.513
Oh, please.

22:07.549 --> 22:09.883
You didn't even have the
guts to cast your own curse.

22:11.753 --> 22:13.352
- [Door bells jingle]
- Regina!

22:13.388 --> 22:15.021
Stay back. I got this.

22:16.425 --> 22:19.625
I should have buried
you in that dwarf mine.

22:19.661 --> 22:21.661
Yes, but you didn't.

22:21.697 --> 22:25.731
And now, thanks to my
sister, your plan is over.

22:25.767 --> 22:29.268
That witch made a fatal mistake...

22:29.304 --> 22:31.905
One you're going to have
to pay for right now.

22:43.085 --> 22:44.517
[Tires squealing]

22:46.655 --> 22:47.687
Miss me?

22:56.273 --> 22:58.431
You know, this whole
driving thing's quite easy

22:58.433 --> 23:00.533
when you're actually
trying to hit something.

23:00.569 --> 23:02.135
[Chuckles]

23:09.111 --> 23:10.776
So, what now?

23:10.812 --> 23:12.878
I'm just supposed to
stare at this blanket

23:12.914 --> 23:14.168
and hope my memories appear?

23:14.171 --> 23:15.715
Your mother doesn't want you
to know why she gave you up,

23:15.717 --> 23:17.550
so that's exactly what
we need to find out.

23:17.586 --> 23:19.418
But this isn't working.

23:19.454 --> 23:21.621
Gold, I get it.

23:21.657 --> 23:23.089
It's okay to be scared.

23:23.125 --> 23:24.757
Miss Swan, you are treading

23:24.793 --> 23:26.626
where few who have dared tread survive.

23:26.662 --> 23:27.994
We're past threats.

23:28.030 --> 23:29.695
I know what you're going through.

23:29.731 --> 23:31.398
This is bigger than
anything you've ever faced.

23:31.400 --> 23:33.499
No curse, no monster

23:33.535 --> 23:35.167
is ever going to be as terrifying

23:35.203 --> 23:38.270
as finding out why you were abandoned.

23:38.306 --> 23:40.139
You think I'm afraid of the truth?

23:40.175 --> 23:41.096
Yeah.

23:41.099 --> 23:42.776
I think it means being
vulnerable, and you and I

23:42.778 --> 23:45.078
are people who are really
bad at being vulnerable.

23:47.949 --> 23:50.216
If you won't do it or you,
then do it for your son.

23:51.987 --> 23:53.620
This is his story, too.

23:55.957 --> 24:00.193
You've come this far,
Father. Just let the rest in.

24:06.702 --> 24:08.568
Okay.

24:15.811 --> 24:20.746
Black Fairy: <i>♪ I cried and called
my sweet bairn's name ♪</i>

24:20.782 --> 24:25.952
<i>♪ But never saw sweet baby again ♪</i>

24:27.089 --> 24:30.089
Shh.

24:30.125 --> 24:32.192
Shh.

24:38.266 --> 24:39.432
Where are we?

24:40.769 --> 24:42.802
The Sacred Vault of the Fairies.

24:42.838 --> 24:46.539
Gideon: I heard tales of it as a child.

24:46.575 --> 24:48.908
Mr. Gold: It looks like
your little trick worked,

24:48.944 --> 24:51.410
Miss Swan.

24:51.446 --> 24:53.213
That's my mother.

24:55.751 --> 24:57.851
And that's me.

25:00.655 --> 25:03.656
So, your mother wasn't
always the Black Fairy.

25:03.692 --> 25:07.227
Tiger Lily, do you know
where the wolfsbane is?

25:07.262 --> 25:09.628
It's the last ingredient.

25:09.664 --> 25:12.898
Do you have any idea
how dangerous that is?

25:12.934 --> 25:14.801
What kind of spell is this, anyway?

25:18.607 --> 25:20.506
No.

25:20.542 --> 25:22.942
No, this isn't a spell at all.

25:22.978 --> 25:24.009
This is a curse.

25:24.045 --> 25:25.344
Call it what you want.

25:25.380 --> 25:27.012
It will protect my child.

25:27.048 --> 25:28.715
I found what I need.

25:32.888 --> 25:34.287
It'll all be over soon.

25:36.491 --> 25:38.390
I'm sorry. I can't let you cast this.

25:38.426 --> 25:40.960
You're his fairy godmother.

25:40.996 --> 25:42.261
Why won't you let me save him?

25:42.297 --> 25:44.163
Because the cost is too high.

25:44.199 --> 25:45.598
You're trying to create something

25:45.634 --> 25:46.932
that never should be...

25:46.968 --> 25:50.937
A terrible curse, a dark curse.

25:52.207 --> 25:54.306
It will save my son.

25:54.342 --> 25:58.210
It will send the child destined
to destroy him far away,

25:58.246 --> 26:00.146
to a land without magic.

26:00.182 --> 26:02.949
Not just that child... It
will banish every child.

26:04.085 --> 26:06.118
It's the only way to be sure.

26:06.154 --> 26:10.055
Please, I have to save him.

26:10.091 --> 26:13.259
Aren't fairies supposed
to protect children?

26:13.295 --> 26:16.796
I am, and so is your son.

26:16.816 --> 26:20.416
He's destined to die so
that other children may live.

26:20.468 --> 26:22.335
That is the fate of the Savior.

26:28.109 --> 26:29.408
No.

26:29.444 --> 26:33.078
Savior or not, I will
not let my son die.

26:33.114 --> 26:34.079
[Grunts]

26:34.115 --> 26:35.214
[Gasps]

26:35.250 --> 26:38.250
[Heart beating]

26:38.286 --> 26:42.488
And if I have to kill his own
fairy godmother to protect him,

26:42.524 --> 26:45.624
then that's exactly what I'll do.

26:45.660 --> 26:46.960
[Groans]

26:59.040 --> 27:01.841
[Exhales deeply]

27:01.877 --> 27:03.776
"And you will know the great evil

27:03.812 --> 27:06.379
by the crescent it bears."

27:09.651 --> 27:11.618
Evil was not born this winter.

27:14.422 --> 27:15.821
It was made.

27:15.857 --> 27:17.289
That's not possible.

27:17.325 --> 27:20.526
Fiona... it's you.

27:20.562 --> 27:22.762
You are the great evil.

27:24.933 --> 27:27.934
You and your son are destined
to destroy each other.

27:34.109 --> 27:36.609
[Breathing heavily]

27:43.718 --> 27:47.586
Now that nap time's over,
it's time for battle.

27:47.622 --> 27:48.988
You found the other half.

27:49.024 --> 27:50.456
Indeed I did.

27:50.492 --> 27:52.291
Now let's go de-wing that bat.

27:52.327 --> 27:55.961
Actually... I don't think I'm the Savior

27:55.997 --> 27:57.864
that's supposed to
fight the Black Fairy.

28:00.035 --> 28:03.536
Gold... this is on you.

28:04.940 --> 28:07.206
Wait. Gold is a Savior?

28:07.242 --> 28:09.008
Rumple, is this true?

28:10.645 --> 28:12.078
Yes, it's true.

28:15.784 --> 28:17.883
All these years...

28:17.919 --> 28:18.984
All these years I've known

28:19.020 --> 28:21.954
there was a good man behind the beast.

28:21.990 --> 28:24.190
Now you know it, too.

28:25.627 --> 28:26.960
I don't know what I know...

28:31.766 --> 28:33.199
but I know I must do this.

28:34.869 --> 28:35.968
Let me help you. I can...

28:36.004 --> 28:39.305
No. I've put you in enough danger.

28:39.341 --> 28:43.542
♪

28:43.578 --> 28:46.400
I think it's best that
I face my mother alone.

28:59.445 --> 29:04.048
I see you've mended that dreadful thing.

29:06.953 --> 29:12.723
This wand was meant to
destroy you... as was I.

29:18.064 --> 29:19.763
You found out.

29:21.901 --> 29:25.302
In some ways, I always knew.

29:25.338 --> 29:27.171
Just needed to remember.

29:29.408 --> 29:32.442
I was meant to be the Savior, Mother.

29:32.478 --> 29:36.479
You were just afraid
that I would kill you,

29:36.515 --> 29:38.515
and that's why you left me.

29:38.551 --> 29:40.417
That's what you think?

29:40.453 --> 29:42.185
[Chuckles]

29:42.221 --> 29:43.787
All that effort,

29:43.823 --> 29:46.022
and you didn't even find
what you were looking for.

29:46.058 --> 29:47.057
No, no, no.

29:47.093 --> 29:48.859
Your mind games won't work anymore.

29:50.161 --> 29:53.028
Don't you want the real
answer to your question?

29:53.064 --> 29:54.463
I have my answer.

29:54.499 --> 29:56.098
You have <i> an</i> answer.

29:56.134 --> 30:00.836
You of all people know...
there's always more.

30:02.907 --> 30:05.374
What more, Mother?

30:05.410 --> 30:08.877
Why did you leave me?

30:08.913 --> 30:12.347
Why don't I...

30:12.383 --> 30:15.885
show you what happened?

30:17.422 --> 30:20.355
Please don't do this, Fiona.

30:20.391 --> 30:22.457
We can find another way, together.

30:22.493 --> 30:25.327
We already tried that and failed.

30:25.363 --> 30:26.695
Enough!

30:29.300 --> 30:32.001
No one will be crushing
any hearts today.

30:35.173 --> 30:36.972
So, you both want the same thing...

30:37.008 --> 30:40.575
To see my son die at my hand?

30:40.611 --> 30:43.479
I think I know how I
can break your destiny.

30:46.477 --> 30:48.517
These shears can sever your fate.

30:48.553 --> 30:50.186
Sacrifice your powers

30:50.221 --> 30:52.220
and you will no longer
be the great evil.

30:52.256 --> 30:55.257
You won't be responsible
for your son's death.

30:55.293 --> 30:56.992
No.

30:57.028 --> 31:00.228
I need my power.

31:00.264 --> 31:02.798
If I sever <i> his</i> destiny,

31:02.834 --> 31:04.866
we can be together,

31:04.902 --> 31:07.670
and I will still be strong
enough to protect him.

31:10.808 --> 31:12.240
Fiona, no.

31:12.276 --> 31:13.942
Don't do this.

31:13.978 --> 31:16.578
Your son is destined to be a great hero.

31:16.614 --> 31:19.748
Do not take that from him.
You do not need the power.

31:19.784 --> 31:22.585
Don't tell me what I need.

31:28.326 --> 31:29.792
Aah!

31:33.264 --> 31:34.596
I promise you, son,

31:34.632 --> 31:37.232
I will spend every moment of every day

31:37.268 --> 31:39.969
trying to find my way back to you!

31:49.080 --> 31:50.813
Why didn't you tell me?

31:52.683 --> 31:55.417
Why did you want me to
believe you hated me?

31:55.453 --> 31:59.454
I was banished to that
empty, wretched place, Rumple.

31:59.481 --> 32:03.182
It was easier to let you hate me,

32:03.227 --> 32:06.328
at least until we found a
way for us to be together.

32:06.364 --> 32:08.096
You didn't have to be banished.

32:08.132 --> 32:12.634
You chose your power over mine.

32:12.670 --> 32:14.688
I was trying to protect you.

32:17.508 --> 32:21.977
As someone who has made
the very same decision,

32:22.013 --> 32:25.146
I know a lie when I hear it.

32:25.182 --> 32:29.451
You sentenced me to a life of cowardice.

32:29.487 --> 32:34.656
I altered your fate so that
we could be a family together.

32:34.692 --> 32:38.760
Everything I did was
for you, to protect you.

32:38.796 --> 32:42.665
It's a vile, dangerous world, son.

32:44.201 --> 32:49.237
Because of villains like you...

32:49.273 --> 32:50.606
and me.

32:57.748 --> 33:02.251
Then you know that, if
my choice was wrong...

33:04.755 --> 33:07.656
I did it out of love.

33:07.692 --> 33:11.159
I'm sorry I caused you pain.

33:11.195 --> 33:12.828
And what about Gideon?

33:14.098 --> 33:15.931
What about all the pain you caused him?

33:15.967 --> 33:18.634
That pain made him strong.

33:21.505 --> 33:24.406
It seems...

33:24.442 --> 33:29.811
our family's history spins
on a dark, endless wheel.

33:29.847 --> 33:34.716
I became the Dark One to save
Baelfire from the Ogres War,

33:34.752 --> 33:39.220
and I tried to sever
Gideon from his fate...

33:39.256 --> 33:41.557
so that he wouldn't hate me.

33:44.261 --> 33:47.296
So, you understand what I've done.

33:52.036 --> 33:53.602
I love you.

33:56.841 --> 34:00.242
And now we can finally be a family...

34:04.181 --> 34:06.315
if you'll forgive me.

34:10.721 --> 34:12.721
Can you?

34:12.757 --> 34:16.225
♪

34:30.693 --> 34:33.460
[Tinkling]

34:36.099 --> 34:37.498
Fiona.

34:42.438 --> 34:44.804
Where is Fiona?

34:50.801 --> 34:53.000
She isn't coming back, is she?

34:53.036 --> 34:54.803
I'm afraid not.

34:56.393 --> 34:58.259
Tiger Lily: It was an accident.

34:58.295 --> 35:00.428
She was trying to protect your son.

35:00.464 --> 35:03.631
Of course she was.

35:03.667 --> 35:07.702
There's none more caring
in all of the realms...

35:07.738 --> 35:11.973
Only one of the infinite reasons
why she was the love of my life.

35:14.378 --> 35:16.711
And now <i> he</i> will
be the love of your life.

35:16.747 --> 35:18.346
How?

35:19.950 --> 35:21.949
How can I raise him alone?

35:21.985 --> 35:24.018
By trying.

35:24.054 --> 35:26.988
Your son needs his father now.

35:27.024 --> 35:30.358
And he also needs a name,
so why don't you start there?

35:30.394 --> 35:33.861
[Crying]

35:33.897 --> 35:37.231
Once, this child was perfect.

35:37.267 --> 35:41.369
He was supposed to bring
great light to our lives.

35:46.343 --> 35:49.778
But now my wife is dead, thanks to him.

35:54.485 --> 35:56.218
I know a name perfect.

36:00.257 --> 36:03.491
Rumplestiltskin.

36:03.527 --> 36:07.562
[Crying]

36:11.101 --> 36:12.834
Is that...

36:12.870 --> 36:16.037
Hers, yes.

36:18.342 --> 36:21.076
The Black Fairy has
been banished for good.

36:22.045 --> 36:23.711
You really did it.

36:23.747 --> 36:25.246
And the Blue Fairy?

36:25.282 --> 36:27.849
Safe... Back with her kind.

36:27.885 --> 36:30.184
All is as it was.

36:30.220 --> 36:32.721
Thank you, Gold.

36:32.756 --> 36:36.057
Snow: Looks like the wedding <i>can</i>
appen tomorrow, thanks to you.

36:39.363 --> 36:41.863
You did good, Savior.

36:45.903 --> 36:49.237
[Heart beating]

36:49.273 --> 36:50.872
[Gasps]

36:56.146 --> 36:57.145
[Sighs]

36:58.615 --> 36:59.781
Thank you, Father.

37:05.756 --> 37:07.522
Welcome home, son.

37:18.235 --> 37:19.968
[Chuckles]

37:23.140 --> 37:26.374
I've missed you so much.

37:26.410 --> 37:28.410
Both of you.

37:30.347 --> 37:33.114
And I'm so sorry I allowed
her to take control of me.

37:33.150 --> 37:35.449
Can you forgive me?

37:35.485 --> 37:38.085
Of course we can.

37:38.121 --> 37:39.854
You were under her control.

37:39.890 --> 37:43.090
I can only imagine how
difficult that was, but look...

37:43.126 --> 37:46.994
You needn't worry about her ever again.

37:47.030 --> 37:48.796
I know how hard that must have been,

37:48.832 --> 37:50.699
facing your mother like that, Rumple.

37:53.804 --> 37:56.103
Well, it's over now.

37:56.139 --> 38:01.309
The Black Fairy will never
again be a problem for us.

38:01.345 --> 38:03.077
I'm proud of you, you know?

38:03.113 --> 38:05.079
You did what you said you would.

38:05.115 --> 38:08.316
You fought for this family.

38:08.352 --> 38:09.684
You saved your son.

38:13.423 --> 38:15.857
I'll make a promise to you, Belle,

38:15.893 --> 38:19.060
and to you, Gideon...

38:19.096 --> 38:22.964
It may not always seem
apparent at the time,

38:23.000 --> 38:26.500
but everything I do is for you,

38:26.536 --> 38:29.303
to keep you safe.

38:29.339 --> 38:32.040
♪

38:37.214 --> 38:40.381
Henry, just the lad I was after.

38:40.417 --> 38:41.849
- That sounds ominous.
- Not at all.

38:41.885 --> 38:44.919
Now, you and I have had quite
a few missions together...

38:44.955 --> 38:47.688
Wookie Prisoner Gag,
our time on the Nautilus.

38:47.724 --> 38:49.791
That was more of a
mishap than a mission.

38:49.826 --> 38:52.526
Well, some were more successful
than others, admittedly,

38:52.562 --> 38:56.130
but... you and I have been
through quite a lot together,

38:56.166 --> 38:57.465
haven't we?

38:57.501 --> 39:00.868
Which is why I'm asking
for your assistance now...

39:00.904 --> 39:04.872
And this might be the most
important mission yet...

39:04.908 --> 39:06.708
Operation Best Man.

39:10.047 --> 39:11.579
Really?

39:11.615 --> 39:13.714
Wow. I'm...

39:13.750 --> 39:15.750
I'm honored. Well, it is an honor,

39:15.786 --> 39:17.785
but with it comes great responsibility.

39:17.821 --> 39:20.722
For the next 24 hours, you and you alone

39:20.757 --> 39:24.592
will be the keeper of this
most valuable treasure...

39:24.628 --> 39:25.593
The wedding rings.

39:25.629 --> 39:27.228
And guard them with your life.

39:27.264 --> 39:31.032
If you lose them, your mother
will most certainly kill you.

39:31.068 --> 39:32.633
His mother will do what now?

39:32.669 --> 39:36.270
Ah, Henry and I were just
discussing business...

39:36.306 --> 39:37.271
Between men.

39:37.307 --> 39:38.239
Hmm.

39:38.275 --> 39:39.407
You can count on me.

39:39.443 --> 39:40.575
I'll see you tomorrow.

39:42.512 --> 39:43.844
Tomorrow? You live here.

39:43.880 --> 39:45.413
Aye, but I'm not staying here tonight.

39:45.449 --> 39:47.311
It's bad luck to see the
bride before the wedding.

39:47.313 --> 39:48.316
You can't be serious.

39:48.352 --> 39:50.751
A seafaring man does not
take superstitions lightly.

39:50.787 --> 39:53.287
The last thing you and I need
is another stitch of bad luck.

39:53.323 --> 39:56.691
After tomorrow, there'll
be no getting rid of me.

39:56.727 --> 39:58.660
- Promise?
- Aye.

40:15.779 --> 40:20.548
Black Fairy: So... did they trust you?

40:20.584 --> 40:22.283
Of course they did.

40:24.721 --> 40:28.622
The heart... They believed it was mine?

40:28.658 --> 40:31.659
No one ever doubts me.

40:32.896 --> 40:37.264
You may have been born
the Savior, but admit it...

40:37.300 --> 40:40.134
You simply adore being the Dark One.

40:40.170 --> 40:44.906
I suppose I do have an affinity
for the darker things in life.

40:46.643 --> 40:50.311
Call it a family trait.

40:50.347 --> 40:53.948
Then I assume you have Belle
and Gideon safely tucked away?

40:53.984 --> 40:57.618
Both peacefully asleep and safe,

40:57.654 --> 40:59.887
with no idea of what's to come.

40:59.923 --> 41:01.255
Good.

41:01.291 --> 41:05.060
Because what's to come,
my beautiful boy...

41:06.830 --> 41:11.032
is, at long last, a happy
ending for our family.

41:13.070 --> 41:15.536
The Final Battle.

41:15.572 --> 41:20.975
You may no longer be the
Savior, but one still stands.

41:21.011 --> 41:23.344
And tomorrow is a very special day

41:23.380 --> 41:24.779
for Emma Swan.

41:24.815 --> 41:26.347
[Chuckles]

41:27.871 --> 41:30.238
Tomorrow is the day she dies.

